Posts.Content: michelle_g wrote: I went to the doc on Monday with blood coming out of my nipple.  Doc told me that there were a couple of possibilities - could be an infection (no swelling, redness or pain) or could be breast cancer.  She immediately made an appointment with the Cancer center (they should call it something else) and took blood.  Tuesday they called & told me that my white cell count was normal - no infection.  I am totally freaking out!  The soonest the Cancer Center could get me in was Friday morning.  I'm scared that I'm still not going to know anything tomorrow.  Michelle Log in to post a reply
